unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, I;

A = (1,2);
B = (0,0);
C = (3,0);
I = incenter(A,B,C);
D = (I + reflect(B,C)*(I))/2;
E = (I + reflect(C,A)*(I))/2;
F = (I + reflect(A,B)*(I))/2;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(incircle(A,B,C));
draw(E--I--F);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, NE);
label("$F$", F, NW);
label("$I$", I, S);
[/asy]

groundtruth:
Since $AE$ and $AF$ are tangents from the same point to the same circle, $AE = AF$.  Let $x = AE = AF$.  Similarly, let $y = BD = BF$ and $z = CD = CE$.

